			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I know priests are for the most part good guys, but I thought I'd share a little story of a good cleric on a bad day. I was in the West Commons, just takin a stroll by the Derv camp to see if my services might be needed. I saw alot of dead bodies lying about. Then I turned to see this Dark Elven SK running east with about 4 or 5 Dervs on his heels. Suddenly, the Dark Elf caught sight of me, turned sharply, and trained the whole lot on ME!!! Of course I ran like hell for the East Commons. I stepped into the East Commons with only a shread of life left. Needless to say, I was pissed. And when the Dark Elf popped into the East Commons, I gave him a good tongue lashing. He tried to deny training them on me, but then finally laughed and said, &quot;So what if I did?&quot; O, I was steamin then. I thought of challenging him to a dual, but he conned high yellow to me, and I had just gained my level and didn't want to risk loosing my new spells. So.....I followed him back to the West Commons. I tailed him from a distance and just watched him solo some mobs. Finally, he came upon a particularly nasty Kodi. The Kodi was mauling him pretty good, but he had the Kodi beat. I saw my chance. I cast my best healing on the Kodi twice, just when it was turning to run. Imagine the shock on that Dark Elfs face when he saw that big ol' nasty bear turn back on him with 90% of its hit points. O, the Dark Elf tried to run, but he was hurt and no match for the speed of that big Kodi. I watched with great amusement as the Kodi laid open the Dark Elf's back with is mighty claws and then proceed to maul his unconsious body to death. Yes, my fellow members of the clergy, it was the God of Vengeance I prayed to that day. He heard my prayers, and I became his messenger. We are good guys most of the time, but to anger us is to invite the wrath of the gods. Let this be a warning to those who tread on us. Step lightly, you don't want to piss us off. As to that Dark Elf, well, let's just say I got to savor my sweet victory when he expressed his anger through 10min of cursing and name-calling. His anger at me only assured me of my victory. I was even there to wave at him when he finally arrived at his corpse (which brought another steady stream of curses). And once, while he was cursing me for killing him, I said, &quot;So what if I did&quot;<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Veldraine<BR>
Priest of the Mother<BR>
Harbinger of Vengeance
