	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I have a few things that I would like to say. Whether or not that Verant reads this is OK with me.  I have very few beefs about the cleric class. I have used to great affect some of the spells that some consider useless.  Invigor I had to use with a lowerlevel friend tank of mine who was fighting a DW Croc in Oasis.  I had tons of mana and he was out of stamina in every fight he was in.  Stun:  This is my bread and butter.  If something is pounding on me, no biggie; Stun, root; move SmiteSmiteSmiteSmite; repeat.  The cleric armor quest that Verant has given to us is a good quest.  Note I said QUEST.  The armor itself stinks.  This is a monumental quest that should have monumental rewards.  By the time you can complete this quest solo OR grouped the armor is worthless.  Probably Verant made this quest for clerics to say &quot;Look what I did!&quot;  Well, not me.  If I wanted notariaty I would have been a Wizard or Warrior.  Another point I want to touch on is our lack of transportation magic or spells in general.  We get Gate and Bind affinity which can set us up nicely for a solo career.  However, having to run like hell from Bouncer Hurd in the Feerrott just to get to Cazik-Thule while wizards teleport in and Invis and cruise to the Courtyard I can even live with.  But the fact that we are cut off from the planes with no Plane Portals is nearly unexceptable.  My reasoning behind this is not just the fact that I want it, no.  It is because it adds some balance to the game and spreads out the responsibility some.  Clerics are rarely taking damage in the Planes unless they just fully healed a tank.  We could get an Evac off quicker than a mage who is getting beat on for dealing a tad too much damage.  <BR>
<BR>
The next thing I want to touch on are some of the uses for the spells we have.<BR>
<BR>
Lull line of spells.  These spells are useful other than pulling only part of a camp. If one of your tanks is getting beat down and the other can't taunt it off, use Calm then have the fresh tank Taunt.  The MoB will most of the time change to the fresh tank and you can commence the healing.  <BR>
<BR>
Buffs (Courage all the way to Valor):  No matter what the tank he will be begging for these buffs.  The added HP and AC are indespensible. They also make soloing much easier in that you will have a lot more hp.<BR>
<BR>
AC Buffs:(Holy armor, etc.)  Again, Great spells. These, along with a Symbol spell and HP/AC buffs make you a decent tank until about 30th level.  Although, I never recommend Tanking something that is making a warrior go, &quot;OUCH&quot;.<BR>
<BR>
Direct Damage (Strike, Furor, Smite, etc.):  Horribly damage to mana ratio, until you hit Smite where it starts to improve.  One thing I forget to mention:  Verant.  What was the point in giving us 15 levels with no new DD spells? The undead spell at 24 doesn't count.  <BR>
<BR>
Undead Damage:  I dare anyone to say that a cleric can't solo ANY undead 3 levels before they should. At 15th level I could take down Ghouls that conned red.  It took my entire mana bar and 99% of my life, but was a recreatable event.  A good blunt weapon will hit more and do higher end damage versus most undead.<BR>
<BR>
Summon Weapons:  Just plain lame.  I have Hammer of Wrath and had to use it once. Mind you ONCE.  A ghoul in E Com camped my body.<BR>
<BR>
Armor:  In the beginning 1-9 go for a suit of leather. 9-15th Banded all the way.  Blackened Iron is also a good choice.  IF you can get it for a non-ludicrous price.  I have Bi on my 21st level cleric and it serves me well.  Seems I take less hits and less damage than with banded and even some bronze.  And my ac is not as good with the BI.  Hmmmmmmm.  When you get to about 20th level then start looking for the high end armor stuff.  BONUSES TO WISDOM!!!!!<BR>
<BR>
Weapons:  Screaming Mace.  'nuff said. Don't go with less.  Keep it until you get Caudecus of Sacrement or Dawnfire(Good luck on both, YOU NEED IT)<BR>
<BR>
To any low level clerics that may be reading this, look me up!  I am always willing to help.  I may have no money like all other clerics, but help I will.<BR>
<BR>
Aeolwind Stormrunner<BR>
Order of Divine Winds<BR>
21st Season Cleric of Tunare<BR>
Erolissi Marr server<BR>
&quot;May the Winds guide and protect thee&quot;<BR>
<BR>
<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
