				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I have noticed all the comments on a Cleric being boring. I would like to add my arguement on why the Cleric is not boring.<BR>
<BR>
1. A cleric is a healer and what is better than sitting back watching the full battle while tanks and casters do the dmg and when one gets low you cast that heal that saves there life and the groups. (Because without the Tank you might not live)<BR>
<BR>
2. While sitting back watching the hp you can see who is taking dmg what is better then when you see a Mage or a Wiz taking dmg to get up cast a heal and then yell someone to taunt off the caster. If they dont do it or cant do it then I will taunt the mob after i get the mob off i will stun him and cast anouther heal on the Mage or Wiz and continue to watch hp. (Still Have Mob on you) after i taunt the mob off the caster if i have to i do not hit them or do DD to them this way when a Tank hits the mob a few times i go to the bottom of his hate list meaning he is not hitting on me anymore. Now I am low on life and need to med so what do i do I cast a heal on anyone in the group that is less than 3 bubbles of life and i sit down to med. While i sit down to med i am regaining the HP that i lost when the mob was hitting me. (A cleric can take a little dmg so make sure the taunt is comming soon) That to me is exciting<BR>
<BR>
Also a tip on the stun spell. This is a very valuable spell who cares if it only stuns for 2 seconds. Do you remember as a caster seeing spell interupted? Guess what if you are fighting a NPC caster you can interupt there spells to and Stun does a good job at it The one thing about stun is it has a slower repop time so now you go back to that lvl 1 spell Strike. It does not do much dmg which is good (because you are a healer) but it will interupt the cast as well and a quick cast time. Dont try this with a big DD though because you may find yourself on the TOP of the Hate List which you maybe be at already when you casted that last heal. Trust me this spell works good Try befallen when you are fighting a necro and your heals are constantly interupted and you have 2 or 3 DOT's stacked on you and your group does as well. You will love stoping there spell so you can cast a heal (or run) I also recommend using a hotkey for these two things RUN RUN RUN GO TO ZONE and the other one should be Good Job Guys! (to congrat the group after a big fight)As a cleric i take it as my job to see when the fight is getting out of hand.<BR>
<BR>
As to heals and buffs on people you dont know DO IT. they will appreciate it everytime i am going to the bank i stop at the newbie log and buff and heal anyone that is sitting on the log or around it. I also go check on the ruins to see if a mummy or zombie has spawned not for me to kill it but to let someone else do it while i heal them and let them get exp. I just dont think the cleric is a boring role i think it is alot of fun and you will make alot of friends. <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Vanygi DE Cleric 13th<BR>
E'CI Server
