	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Alright, here is my experience being a High Elf Cleric up to 26th Level.<BR>
<BR>
First of all, for all the low level clerics out there who think they do good melee damage, expect to be very useless in melee after 20. In fact, level 20-24 sucks.<BR>
<BR>
Starting with 1-9th level, save up all your money for 9th level spells and an RTS. Get your center, root, and if you cannot yet afford a runed totem staff, get hammer of wrath. Ward undead would be nice, but get that later if you can't afford the above. Now, get a friend to help you hunt wisps in west commons. This is great experience, and they drop greater light stones which you can sell for 7pp there for quick money, or you can store them for the quest and get up to 10pp and exp per greater lightstone (look up the quest, it is here somewhere). Not sure at what level you can start soloing wisps, but by the time you can, you should have bought yourself a runed totem staff with that money of yours. I made 60pp killing every wisp I could find one night, and that was just from selling the stones to players for 7pp (not knowing about the quest). Also, if wisp hunting gets tedious, take a break and kill dervs in a group. Sometimes they drop bronze weapons and that is good low level money too.<BR>
<BR>
Now, as to what kind of jewelry you should invest in. I invested in strength jewelry because I had acquired alot of bronze armor at that time. You may prefer to invest in wis stuff if you are a dwarf and already have strength. I bought gold amber earrings, silver amber rings, and I also got some rusty spiked shoulder pads and a bracer of erollisi, along with some other str stuff. This got my str from 75 to 100.<BR>
<BR>
Once I got to level 17, I went to fight orcs in high pass. This is good exp if you are in the group that is getting the kills here. Don't know how it is on other servers, but on Xegony, there are groups KSing from eachother for kills. Get in a group with casters and/or twinks with an exe axe. Your role here will change depending on whether or not you are competing with another group. If you are competing, nuke. If you aren't, heal. At around 20, I replaced all my str jewelry with wis jewelry because It was becoming very apparent that my true job was to be a healer. After I got to 22 fighting orcs, I went to High Keep and grouped in the guard room until 24, then I went to the warrior room. All you will ever do here is heal people. I only went into melee against weaker guard or cabalist spawns or caster goblins that went down quick, but this was just to help my combat skills a bit and break the monotony of heal/med. Getting a job here as a cleric of 24 is easy if not many other clerics are in the zone. Once I got 26, I got sick with the flu and stopped playing for a week. This shouldn't happen to you I hope. :) After I came back, I went around making money to buy some platinum jasper rings. Now maybe I'll go back to high keep.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
