	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ok. I am not going to tell you that clerics are boring since that is a personal opinion everyone is entitled to. I will say this, Clerics can be extremely fun if you like what you do and roleplay them to the max! YOU ARE A HEALER. You are not a nuker (except aginst undead) and you are not a tank. You are a healer. Of course sometimes you will ahve to solo to get that nice XP and here's what I recommend for that. First the soothe line of spells is a beautiful thing. Then use your fear/root/stuns and start nuking with your 75dmg smite. Finally finish them off with the melee and self healing. It may take you a while when you're only doing 17dmg but you'll get there. Finally... Yes clerics are poor classes, I have experienced that, but after the lower levels it's not that bad if you are smart. A couple of easy money making tips:<BR>
1. Normal things you would sell to merchants like bat wings and bone chips, dont! These are stackable so get 20 of them and auction to casters ans necros and sks.<BR>
2. Take up tailoring. Though this may not be the most profitable trade skill in the end, it will do wonders for your income at the lower levels. You'll start with patchwork, getting the ruined pelts you need of easy animals and combining with a 1sp pattern in a 1gp sewing kit, sell to merchants or newbies. Then get some spider (not spiderling) silks form the large spiders in EC or tarantulas, get 2 and combine for silk swatch, combine swatch with pattern and you get armor piece you can auction off to mid level caster for 2 or 3pp. Finally you'll move on to cured silk, tougher and more costly to make but monks pay top pp for this.<BR>
(Jeez I've written a lot, let me finish)<BR>
3. I'm sorry to say this but there are newbies out there that have been given loads of money by friend but have no idea wht things cost, up things 1 or 2 or 10pp when selling to them.<BR>
4. You are a curer/buffer/healer and at lvl 14 binder. No one gives you services for free in real life why should you in EQ?<BR>
5. Learn from the game. In a particular zone there may be items of high demand (ex. Crushbone- bracer of battle-I've seen people paying up to 100pp for this. If you get your hands on it, dont auction it off to the first guy that offers you 30pp, hang on to it for a while, consider other offers... Or give it to me cause I really want the +3 shoulderpiece you trade it in for! JEJE<BR>
I hope I have enlightened newbies and non-newbies alike.<BR>
May Mithaniel Marr protect you in your journeys<BR>
PEACE AND LOVE FROM A PUERTORICAN CLERIC!!!<BR>
<BR>
Albertain<BR>
Povar Cleric of the 16th level
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
